Soulful singer Simi has shared some of the things that she has had to master since she became famous. The mother of one revealed this in a recent tweet.   Fame can be intoxicating, says Mildred Okwo     Age not just a number, says Pete Edochie at 75     You can’t love Wizkid , Davido equally- Cubana Chief Priest   Her tweet reads: “There are so many things that don’t come naturally to me that I’ve had to master because my kadara chose music. Like fame. And networking. And depending on outside opinions. I’m just now seriously coming to terms with how difficult this is for me. Sorry Simi.” In another tweet, she wrote “Most days, I just want to write whatever song I like, read a book and hang out with my daughter…and have someone putting 1m dollar in my acct weekly just for being myself. It’s hard work for my spirit and mind.”